headline: Carrier Sets Benchmark with First U.S. DOE-Validated 10-14-Ton Commercial Rooftop Unit
summary: Carrier Global Corporation (NYSE: CARR), global leader in intelligent climate and energy solutions, today announced it is the first HVAC original equipment manufacturer to complete the U.S. Department of Energy's (DOE) Commercial Building HVAC Technology Challenge laboratory validation in the 10–14-ton rooftop heat pump category. The Carrier system met or exceeded all challenge requirements, including heating capacity and energy efficiency test standards — delivering 100% heating capacity at 5°F

headline: 3 Volatile Stocks with Questionable Fundamentals
summary: Market swings can be tough to stomach, and volatile stocks often experience exaggerated moves in both directions. While many thrive during risk-on environments, many also struggle to maintain investor confidence when the ride gets bumpy.
